Anthony S. D’ANGELO, Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 3, 1928. No. 5180. Hugh S. Suthon and Joseph A. McCaleb, both of New Orleans, La., for plaintiff in error. Wayne G. Borah, U. S. Atty., and Wm. H. Norman, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New Orleans, La.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and POSTER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
